    "AI-Based Pain Assessment ToolsAI-based pain assessment tools utilize various high-tech tools to improve the efficiency, accuracy, and objectivity of pain assessment.",
    "These tools can assist healthcare professionals in properly assessing, diagnosing, monitoring, and managing pain more effectively.",
    "The following represent a few examples of the AI-based tools for pain assessments.",
    "Wearable Devices and Mobile ApplicationsThe World Health Organization defines mobile health technologies as medical and public health practices supported by mobile devices [55].",
    "Smart wearable devices or sensors are AI tools that can enable continuous monitoring of human physiological activities, vital signs, and body movements without any disturbance to the activities of daily living [57]."
